{{Multiple issues| {{Orphan|date=October 2017}} {{one source|date=October 2017}} {{Rough translation|French|date=October 2017}} }} {{Infobox military conflict | conflict = | width = | partof = French Conquest of Algeria | image = | caption = | date = 26-27 june 1835 | place = [[Sig, Algeria|Sig]], [[Algeria]] | coordinates = | map_type = | map_relief = | latitude = | longitude = | map_size = | map_marksize = | map_caption = | map_label = | territory = | result = Algerian Victory | status = | combatants_header = | combatant1 = {{flagicon|France}} [[July Monarchy|France]] | combatant2 = [[File:Dz flag-Abdelkader.png|23px]] [[Emirate of Abdelkader]] | commander1 = [[Camille Alphonse Trézel]] | commander2 = [[Emir Abdelkader]] | units1 = | units2 = | units3 = | strength1 = at least 2500 <ref name="Hugo-1838">Abel Hugo, France militaire. 1838. [https://books.google.fr/books?id=pB5EAAAAYAAJ&printsec=frontcover&hl=fr#v=onepage&q&f=false Histoire des armées françaises], Volume 5, p.360. In French.</ref>(armed) | strength2 = 8,000 cavaliers,4 000 infantrymen<ref name="Hugo-1838" /> | casualties1 = 52 died , 189 wounded<ref name="Hugo-1838" /> | casualties2 = Unknown but low | notes = | campaignbox = {{Campaignbox French conquest of Algeria}} }} '''The Battle of Sig''' took place from 26 to 27 June 1835 in the forest of Moulay Ismael near [[Sig, Algeria|Wadi Sig]] and opposed French forces, assisted by the Douair and Smela tribes, to Algerian resistors led by [[Emir Abdelkader]].
==The battle June 26==
The fighting lasted two days. Unable to resist the Algerian assaults, the men of General [[Camille Alphonse Trézel]] retreated. A further withdrawal was also initiated at [[Arzew]], but Trézel's forces were swiftly overtaken. The Algerian cavalry, faster, more mobile and above all more numerous, blocked the French at the [[Macta]]. The [[French Foreign Legion|Foreign Legion]] succeeded in containing their attackers and repelling them, but the Algerians continued their attacks.
==The ambush June 27 ==
The next day, they ambushed the French at the Macta marshes, formed by the confluence of the [[Sig River|Sig]] and the Habra, between the river and the forest. The heavy wagons of the convoy were destroyed and the wounded from the previous night's battle slaughtered, while the troops of the escort were annihilated. The Foreign Legion again stepped in; they freed the way toward Arzew, but the attack by the Algerian horsemen cost the French forces 52 men killed and 189 wounded.
