The '''Casas de Los Pinos Solar Power Plant''' is a {{nowrap|10 [[Megawatt|MW]]}} [[photovoltaic]] power station in [[Castile-La Mancha]], [[Spain]]. The facility was commissioned in November 2007, and was developed by Renovalia Solar SL. The plant consists of 120&nbsp;[[Solaria]] and [[Suntech]] units of {{nowrap|100 kW}}, with a total of 69,850 [[photovoltaic panels]].<ref>[http://www.exenewable.com/projectProfile.asp?id=12609 Casas de Los Pinos Solar Power Plant] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110710211741/http://www.exenewable.com/projectProfile.asp?id=12609 |date=July 10, 2011 }}</ref>
