{{Infobox airport | name = Chabelley Airport | nativename = | nativename-a = | nativename-r = | image = | image-width = | image2 = | image2-width = | caption = | IATA = | ICAO = HDCH | pushpin_map = Djibouti | pushpin_map_caption = Location of airport in Djibouti | pushpin_label = CBA | pushpin_label_position = left | type = Military | owner = | operator = | city-served = | location = [[Chabelley]], [[Djibouti]] | elevation-f = | elevation-m = 106 | coordinates = {{Coord|11|31|N|43|04|E|type:airport_region:DJ|display=inline,title}} | website = | metric-elev = | metric-rwy = | r1-number = 10/28 | r1-length-f = 8530 | r1-length-m = 2600 | r1-surface = [[Asphalt]] | stat-year = | stat1-header = | stat1-data = | stat2-header = | stat2-data = | footnotes = }}
'''Chabelley Airport''' {{airport codes||HDCH}}, also known as the '''Chabelley Airfield''', is an isolated airstrip in [[Chabelley]], located some 6 miles to the southwest of [[Djibouti City]], the capital of [[Djibouti]].<ref>{{GCM|HDCH}}</ref>
==Military== Although it is operated and used by the French military,<ref name="Reut5jan16">{{cite news |last=Trevithick |first=Joseph |date=5 January 2016 |title=This small airstrip is the future of America’s way of war |url=http://blogs.reuters.com/great-debate/2016/01/05/this-small-airstrip-is-the-future-of-americas-way-of-war/ |newspaper=Reuters |access-date=14 January 2016}}</ref> in September 2013, it began serving as a temporary base for [[United States Armed Forces|U.S. military]] [[unmanned aircraft]].<ref name="Umdffdsc" /><ref name="Lcdlesm" /> The move came after the Djiboutian government expressed concern over a number of recent drone mishaps and accidents at the American [[Camp Lemonnier]] Naval Expeditionary Base, which serves as a hub for counterterrorism operations in [[Yemen]] and [[Somalia]]. The Djiboutian authorities consequently asked U.S. officials to relocate the drones to the rarely used Chabelley Airfield.<ref name="Umdffdsc">{{cite news|first1=Craig|last1=Whitlock|first2=Greg|last2=Miller|title=U.S. moves drone fleet from Camp Lemonnier to ease Djibouti’s safety concerns|url=https://articles.washingtonpost.com/2013-09-24/world/42357265_1_drone-operations-drone-flights-drone-strikes|accessdate=20 November 2013|newspaper=[[Washington Post]]|date=24 September 2013}}</ref> Thitherto, the Chabelley airstrip had been exclusively reserved in case of need for French military devices.<ref name="Lcdlesm">{{cite news|title=La Corne de l’Afrique, enjeu stratégique majeur |url=http://www.assajog.com/la-corne-de-lafrique-enjeu-strategique-majeur/ |accessdate=20 November 2013 |newspaper=Assajog |date=17 November 2013 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131120093853/http://www.assajog.com/la-corne-de-lafrique-enjeu-strategique-majeur/ |archivedate=November 20, 2013 |language=fr}}</ref> The [[United States Air Force|U.S. Air Force’s]] 870th Air Expeditionary Squadron operates from the airfield.<ref name="Reut5jan16" />
