'''Fjernsynsteatret''' was a department of the [[Norwegian Broadcasting Corporation]] (NRK) which produced plays for television broadcasting. It opened in 1960 (after about a year of experimental operation), and operated until 1990, when a major reorganisation of NRK took place.<ref name=snl-ft>{{cite encyclopedia |year=2007 |title=Fjernsynsteatret |encyclopedia=[[Store norske leksikon]] |first=Svend Erik Løken |last=Larsen |publisher=Kunnskapsforlaget |location=Oslo  |url=http://www.snl.no/Fjernsynsteatret |language=Norwegian | accessdate=19 April 2009 }}</ref>

Its first leader was [[Arild Brinchmann]], who headed the theatre from its start until 1967.<ref name=snl-ft/><ref name=ab>{{cite encyclopedia |year=2007 |title=Arild Brinchmann |encyclopedia=Store norske leksikon |publisher=Kunnskapsforlaget |location=Oslo |url=http://www.snl.no/Arild_Brinchmann |language=Norwegian | accessdate=19 April 2009 }}</ref>  Later directors were [[Tore Breda Thoresen]] from 1967 to 1980,<ref name=tbt>{{cite encyclopedia |year=2007 |title=Tore Breda Thoresen |encyclopedia=Store norske leksikon |publisher=Kunnskapsforlaget |location=Oslo |url=http://www.snl.no/Tore_Breda_Thoresen |language=Norwegian | accessdate=19 April 2009 }}</ref>  and [[Magne Bleness]] from 1980 to 1990.<ref name=snl-ft/><ref name=mb>{{cite encyclopedia |year=2007 |title=Magne Bleness |encyclopedia=Store norske leksikon |publisher=Kunnskapsforlaget |location=Oslo |url=http://www.snl.no/Magne_Bleness |language=Norwegian | accessdate=19 April 2009 }}</ref>

Fjernsynsteatret's first production was a play by [[Peter Brook]], shown 8 April 1959. The first years the theatre developed between twenty and twenty-five productions annually, and the performances were broadcast directly. Later developments saw a merge between theatre and film, the productions became more expensive, and the number of productions decreased significantly.<ref name=snl-ft/>

The theatre was replaced by ''NRK Drama'' in 1990.<ref name=snl-ft/>

