{{Infobox laboratory | name = NASU Institute for Environment Geochemistry | image = | established = 1996 | operating_agency = [[National Academy of Sciences of Ukraine]] | director = Heorhiy Vitaliyovych Lysychenko | address = Prospekt Akademika Palladina, 34a, [[Kiev]], [[Ukraine]] 03680 | website = [http://www.igns.gov.ua www.igns.gov.ua] |}}
'''Institute for Environment Geochemistry of the [[National Academy of Sciences of Ukraine]]''' ('''KINR''') ({{lang-ua|Інститут геохімії навколишнього середовища НАН України}}) located in [[Kiev]], [[Ukraine]].
==History== Decision on creation of the institute with dual subordination to the [[National Academy of Sciences of Ukraine]] and the [[Ministry of Emergencies (Ukraine)|Ministry of Emergencies]] was adopted on 29 December 1995. On 4 January 1996 a joint order of the Academy and the Ministry was signed by [[Borys Paton]] and [[Volodymyr Kholosha]] (acting minister) on creation of the State science center of Surrounding Environment Radiation- and Geochemistry based on two departments of the NASU Institute of Geochemistry, Mineralogy, and Ore-creation (Department of surrounding environment radiation- and geochemistry and Department of [[metallogeny]]).
On 12 July 2000 the center was renamed as the NASU Institute of [Surrounding] Environment Geochemistry.
In 2012 the Ministry of Emergencies was liquidated (degraded to a state service under Ministry of Internal Affairs).
==Directors== * 1996 — 2013 [[Emlen Sobotovych]] * 2013 — [[Heorhiy Lysychenko]]
==Associated entities== * Kiev science and production association "Ekolohichni tekhnolohiyi i normatyvy" (Ecological technologies and norms) * State science and production small enterprise "Vidrodzhenia" (Revival) * State enterprise "Ekoinform" * Interagency scientific council on issues of radioactive waste management (Presidium of the NASU) * Committee on meteorites (Department of Earth Sciences of the Presidium of the NASU) * Branch of the [[National Aviation University]] Ecology Department * The [[National Aviation University]] Ecology Department jointly with the [[National Aviation University]] Institute of Land Management and Information Technology * NASU Center for collective use of unique scientific instruments "Mineraloho-heokhimichni doslidzhenia" (Mineral and geochemical research) * others
