{{Infobox WorldScouting | name =The Gambia Scout Association | image =Gambia Scout Association.svg | caption = | type = | owner = | age = | headquarters = | location = | country =The Gambia | coords = | f-date =1921 | defunct = | founders = | founder = | award-for = | members =18,448 | chiefscouttitle = chief | chiefscouttitle2 = | chiefscout2 = | chiefscouttitle3 = | chiefscout3 = | website = | affiliation =[[World Organization of the Scout Movement]] | next = | prev = }}
'''The Gambia Scout Association''', the national [[scouting]] organization of [[the Gambia]], was founded in 1921, and became a member of the [[World Organization of the Scout Movement]] in 1984.
== Activities == [[File:US and Gambian Scouts (5998122274).jpg|thumb|left]]
The coeducational Gambia Scout Association has 18,448 members as of 2008.<ref name="WOSM-TR_05-08">{{cite web |title=Triennial Report 2005-2008 |url=http://scout.org/en/content/download/11615/94838/file/Triennial_Report_EN.pdf |publisher=World Organization of the Scout Movement |accessdate=2008-07-13 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080909204757/http://scout.org/en/content/download/11615/94838/file/Triennial_Report_EN.pdf |archivedate=2008-09-09 |df= }}</ref>
Special activities include community service projects such as tree planting. Scouts regularly participate in camping and hiking. [[Music]] is also a very important part of Scouting in the Gambia, but because there is little money for instruments and [[sheet music]], there is a waiting list to get into the Scout band, and they learn all their music by ear. {{Citation needed|date=June 2009}}
== Presidents == *[[Alhaji Alieu Ebrima Cham Joof]] served the movement from 1938 to 2005; former President of the Gambia National Scout Council; scholar on the history of scouting in the Gambia; and first Gambian to be awarded the [[Wood Badge]].<ref>[[Foroyaa]]: Exclusive Interview with Foroyaa Panorama: {{cite web |url=http://www.foroyaa.gm/modules/news/article.php?storyid=6832 |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2011-10-03 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20111003130110/http://www.foroyaa.gm/modules/news/article.php?storyid=6832 |archivedate=2011-10-03 |df= }}</ref><ref>The Point Newspaper: [http://thepoint.gm/africa/gambia/article/tribute-to-late-alhagie-a-e-cham-joof "Tribute to Late Alhagie A. E. Cham Joof", by Mr Momodou Jammeh]</ref> *In 2007, David Hafner replaced Alieu Mamar Njie as chief [[commissioner]].
== Controversies == In September 2015, six executives of the association were arrested for conspiracy to commit a felony, obtaining money by false pretence and stealing a motor vehicle.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://thepoint.gm/africa/gambia/article/six-gambia-scout-association-executive-members-remanded|title=Six Gambia Scout Association executive members remanded|website=Thepoint.gm|date=10 September 2015|access-date=21 November 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://allafrica.com/stories/201511021393.html|title=Gambia: In Gambia Scout Association Case, More Charges to Be Instituted|website=Allafrica.com|date=2 November 2015|access-date=21 November 2016}}</ref>
